overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all specified acceptance criteria. The assistant
  conducted a detailed analysis, identified several missing features and areas
  for improvement, and then systematically implemented these changes. Key
  enhancements included adding a critical tiredness severity scale with safety
  warnings, implementing detection and reporting for complex sleep disorders
  like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and refining the scoring for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. The application's data export capabilities were
  significantly improved by expanding the CSV to include all questionnaire
  responses. Additionally, new questions were integrated to screen for
  pain-related sleep issues and chronic fatigue, and placeholder links to
  external resources were added to the generated reports. The process involved
  extensive modifications to data structures, validation logic, UI components,
  and reporting functionalities, ensuring a more robust and informative user
  experience. The final task of adding medical/mental health history questions
  was in progress when the conversation ended.
